Assistant Brand Manager for Malta Guinness, Ife Odedere has stated that every Nigerian needs refueling irrespective of their location or occupation. Odedere made this statement during the team’s visit to the Muslim faithful in Abuja, Kaduna and Kano. According to him, Malta Guinness team is in the business of fueling the greatness of Nigerians with Malta Guinness filled with Vitamins B1, B2, B3, B5 and B6, which revitalizes the body. In Odedere’s words: “Malta Guinness is reaffirming its position as the number one non-alcoholic Malt drink that fuels the greatness of Nigerians everywhere, no matter where they are or what they do.” “We have visited Muslim faithful in the cities of Abuja, Kaduna, Kano and Bauchi. And I tell you that these visits have provided us with a platform to showcase the energy-giving attributes of Malta Guinness- Vitamins B1, B2, B3, B5 and B6 which revitalizes the body,” he added. The Malta Guinness team also donated ablution Kettles to the Mosques they visited. In addition to these Mosque visits, Malta Guinness is also supporting a good number of Muslim religious programs on TV and Radio stations to educate and inform Muslims.